      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANItalian shipyard Rosetti Superyachts has unveiled its new luxury yacht that is designed to look like an orca.Project Orca will be 65 meters long and consist of four decks, SuperYacht Times reports. The ship will have a range of 5,000 miles and will be able to travel at a cruising speed of 12 knots.The yacht itself comes with several deck configurations. In its standard configuration, the vessel will have an open deck, a touch-and-go helipad, and snow sledges.The superyacht may also be modified to include an infinity pool, or a raised helipad with a pool and spa area in its interior.Project Orca's interior includes six cabins, which can accommodate up to 12 people along with a crew of 12. The lower deck will also be equipped with a garage to store equipment like jet skis.Fulvio Dodich, CEO and chairman of Rosetti Superyachts, said that the yacht will take approximately 36 months to be built.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. New luxury superyacht2. Length of the vessel, its range and cruising speed3. Different deck configurations of the yacht4. Interior of the yachtVOICEOVER (in English): "Italian shipyard Rosetti Superyachts has unveiled its new luxury yacht that is designed to look like an orca.""SuperYacht Times reports that Project Orca will be 65 meters long and consist of four decks.""The ship will have a range of 5,000 miles and will be able to travel at a cruising speed of 12 knots.""The yacht itself comes with several deck configurations.""In its standard configuration, the vessel will have an open deck, a touch-and-go helipad, and snow sledges.""The superyacht may also be modified to include an infinity pool, or a raised helipad with a pool and spa area in its interior."