ccording to NASA, the X-59's shape is specially designed to mitigate sonic boom by reducing the noise that reaches the ground.""Lockheed Martin says that the airplane makes 75 Perceived Level decibels, or about as loud as a closing car door.""According to NASA, the jet will feature cameras and sensors that allow safe flying without a forward-facing window.""NASA says the finished jet will fly over select US communities to create instrument readings and to measure the public's opinion."SOURCES:  NASA, Lockheed Martinhttps://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-s-x-59-quiet-supersonic-research-aircraft-cleared-for-final-assemblyhttps://www.lockheedmartin.com/en-us/products/quesst.html***]]></description>
